data.enText: that must be paid or can be paid
A 10% deposit is payable in advance.

data.chText: 本价格可按月分期付款。
data.enText: The price is payable in monthly instalments.

data.chText: 应付予（抬头人、收款人等）
data.enText: when a cheque, etc. is made payable to sb, their name is written on it and they can then pay it into their bank account

means: 应付予(抬头人、收款人等)

tr: a liability account showing how much is owed for goods and services purchased on credit
example: the problem was to match receivables and payables in the same currency

tr: subject to or requiring payment especially as specified
example: a check payable to John Doe

value.def: If an amount of money is payable, it has to be paid or it can be paid.

example.ex: Purchase tax was not payable on goods for export.
example.tran: 出口商品不需要交购买税。

value.def: If a cheque or postal order is made payable to you, it has your name written on it to indicate that you are the person who will receive the money.

example.ex: Write, enclosing a cheque made payable to Cobuild Limited.
example.tran: 写封信，附上一张支付给Cobuild有限公司的支票。
